From James Callison Subject Re SHO and SC In article David Hwang writes In article wrat wharfie writes In article Chris Silvester writes WAGON which I have heard is somehow slightly faster than the Wagon has an automatic it's Could be due to the rear end ratio Usually automatics have different rear ends than manuals from my limited experience You'll have fun looking for the rear end gears on an SHO the Taurus is a front wheel drive I went back and checked the article again The SHO Wagon is quicker than the SHO automatic but significantly slower than the REAL Why anyone would order an SHO with an automatic transmission is beyond me if you can't handle a stick you should stick with a regular Taurus and leave the SHO to real That is not to say that there aren't real drivers who can't use the stick eg disabled persons but they aren't in any position to use an SHO I would be willing to bet that if we removed the automatic transmissions from all performance type cars like the Mustangs Camaros and the like we'd cut down on the number of accidents each Autos are fine for sedate little sedans but they have no business in performance cars James James Callison Microcomputer Coordinator U of Oklahoma Law Center C C DISCLAIMER I'm not an engineer but I play one at The forecast calls for ' T Bird SC It's a hell of a thing killing a You take away all he has and all he's ever gonna Will Munny Unforgiven